Step 1: Determine total liabilities as of the end date.  
 • In this balance sheet, total liabilities can be derived by subtracting Total Owner's Equity from Total Liabilities and Owner's Equity.  
 • Total Liabilities and Owner's Equity = 33,610,271.98  
 • Total Owner's Equity = 29,290,835.16  
 • Total Liabilities = 33,610,271.98 − 29,290,835.16 = 4,319,436.82

Step 2: Determine total assets as of the end date.  
 • Total Assets = 33,610,271.98

Step 3: Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio.  
 • Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets  
 • = 4,319,436.82 / 33,610,271.98 ≈ 0.1285  
 • Rounding to two decimal places gives approximately 0.13

Thus, the final answer is:
